## [**Summary**](https://deliveroo.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ED/pages/4702994438/Summary)

The project aims to improve the login experience of the customer. Currently, each additional step‚Äîlike password resets or forgotten details‚Äîintroduces friction that risks customer drop-off and stunts growth. Every lost login is a missed opportunity.

Our aspiration is to convert login from a point of friction into a growth engine. By making access effortless, secure, and flexible, we aim to unlock growth in Monthly Active Users (MAUs) and drive incremental Gross Transaction Value (GTV). The long-term vision is to position login not just as an access point, but as a key driver of platform engagement, retention, and conversion.

# [**Problem Statement**](https://deliveroo.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ED/pages/2651488295/Writing+a+design+document#Writing-a-Problem-Statement)

Our current account creation and login flows present a significant barrier to user conversion and engagement. In the UKI market, 8-13% of users abandon the sign-up or login process, and an additional 6-8% of login attempts fail outright. This friction is especially detrimental for new and low-frequency users, who represent 75% of visitors but account for only 30% of orders‚Äîa gap likely exacerbated by these access challenges.

# [**Overview**](https://deliveroo.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ED/pages/2651488295/Writing+a+design+document#Giving-an-Overview-and-declaring-Goals)

The login experience is a key driver of growth. Reducing friction at this step can directly improve monthly active users (MAUs) and generate incremental GTV by increasing the number of customers who successfully log in, thereby exposing them to better personalisation based on their order history, saved payment methods, relevant promotions etc.

We aim to prioritise passwordless login options \- not to fully remove passwords, but to reorder the hierarchy of login methods so that frictionless authentication becomes the default. Password login should remain as a supported option for customers who prefer it, but we will increasingly emphasise lower-friction alternatives and push consumers down passwordless routes.

This approach balances **security, simplicity, and accessibility**, creating a seamless experience for most users while still providing reliable backup options.

# **Current Behaviour**

In the existing magic link login flow, users begin by selecting the "Continue with email" option on the login screen. They are prompted to enter their email address, after which they can choose to send a magic link to that address or type password. If the user selects ‚Äúsend magic link‚Äù . The user then receives an email containing the magic link. Clicking the link redirects the user back to the Deliveroo app, where they are automatically logged in

SMS OTP signup flow:  
When the user enters the email address to login but the email address doesn‚Äôt exists, then customers are redirected to SMS flow where the customer enters their phone number and gets the OTP and then continues the signup flow

# [**Proposal**](https://deliveroo.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ED/pages/2654372020/Proposal)

To reduce friction, increase conversion, and improve security, we propose a hierarchical login flow that prioritises passwordless and context-aware authentication methods, while maintaining robust fallback options. The aim is to streamline the experience for users‚Äîespecially new and low-frequency visitors‚Äîwithout compromising on account security.

The requirements have been phased out as PHASE-1 and PHASE-2

#### **PHASE-1:**

**1\. Login Method Hierarchy**

* **Primary options**  
  * **Enter email address** 

**2\. Smart Fallback and Error Handling**

Email as an Identifier : If a user inputs an email address as their identifier then there is experimental flag on backend side which will decide which mechanism will be used for users to login :

1.  If user will belong for Email cohort then:  
- The primary auth method should still be SMS \- however if this fails, then we should send the magic link to the email.  
2. If User belongs to SMS cohort then:  
- the primary auth method would be SMS   
  **Fallback Options will be available on different screens:**  
1. **Resend the code**  
2. **Verify with email \-\> Resend Link**  
3. **Use password**

#### **PHASE-2:**

**1\. Login Method Hierarchy**

* **Primary options**  
  * **Enter phone number**  
* **Secondary options** :   
  * **Enter email address** 

**2\. Smart Fallback and Error Handling**

**Primary Authentication Method: Phone as an identifier**  
Always default to **SMS-based phone number verification** where available. This remains the preferred method due to its speed, familiarity, and high success rate across devices.

**Email as an Identifier :**  
Email as an Identifier : If a user inputs an email address as their identifier then there is experimental flag on backend side which will decide which mechanism will be used for users to login :

3.  If user will belong for Email cohort then:  
- The primary auth method should still be SMS \- however if this fails, then we should send the magic link to the email.  
4. If User belongs to SMS cohort then:  
- the primary auth method would be SMS  
  **Fallback Options will be available on different screens:**  
4. **Resend the code**  
5. **Verify with email \-\> Resend Link**  
6. **Use password**

### **Feature Flag:** 

1. Client side feature flag:  
   **enable\_efforless\_login\_flow:** true/false  
   This feature flag will determine which flow should be shown to user \- old login flow or new login flow.

2. Backend side feature flag:  
   **auth-email-sms-login-flow:**  
   We will introduce a backend-controlled **experimental flag** to govern the login flow logic when a user enters an **email address** as their identifier. This flag will determine- based on predefined experimentation cohorts or percentages‚Äîwhether to:  
* **Trigger SMS-based OTP** as the primary authentication method, or  
* **Send an email-based magic link** automatically as the login method.

# **Backend API details**

* #### **Create new API in co-accounts:-  /request-login**

Create new API (e.g., POST /request-login) 

**Request:**

POST /consumer/accounts/request-login  
      {  
            ‚Äúemail‚Äù: "[swati.sinha@deliveroo.com](mailto:swati.sinha@deliveroo.com)",  
            ‚Äúphone‚Äù: ‚Äú+918972197398‚Äù,  
            "primary\_mechanism": "email"       // email / sms  
            "is\_fallback\_option": true                // true/false  
       }

**In payload \- Mandatory params:**

email  
primary\_mechanism  
is\_fallback\_option

**primary\_mechanism  \-** client will send this value on the basis of below rules:  
**email  :** 1\. When user enter email initially   
            2\. If user is in fallback option then client will send ‚Äúemail‚Äù as primary\_mechanism in case user is trying to login with ‚Äúverify by email‚Äù / ‚Äúresend link‚Äù

**sms  :**       1\. When user enter phone number initially  
              2\. If user is in fallback option then client will send ‚Äúsms‚Äù as  primary\_mechanism in case user is trying to login with ‚Äúresend code‚Äù

#### **Purpose**

The /request-login API initiates the authentication process when a user provides either an email address or a phone number.

**If user enters the email:**  
It intelligently determines whether to send an OTP via SMS or a magic link via email, based on the user‚Äôs cohort, SSO status, platform type, and registration status. In case the primary method for the user id OTP via SMS and SMS failed, then this api internally will send magic link on the user's email address.

**If user enters the phone number:**  
It will send an OTP via SMS after doing the SSO status, platform type, and registration status check on the linked email address of the user. 

##### ---

**Flow Overview**

###### ***Step 1: User Input Checkpoint***

* **Validate incoming payload:**  
  * If **neither email nor phone** is provided ‚Üí return 400 Bad Request: "Missing email or phone input"  
  * If **email is provided** ‚Üí route to **Email Login Journey**  
    If **phone is provided** ‚Üí route to **Phone Login Journey**

---

###### ***Step 2: If User Enters Email / phone number***

1. **Sanitize the Email**  
   * Trim leading/trailing whitespace and convert to lowercase to ensure consistency.

2. **Extract Request Context**  
   * Capture platform type (web, iOS, Android), request locale, headers, client properties.  
   * These are used later for SSO branching and localisation.

3. **Check for SSO Eligibility**  
   * Determine if SSO is enabled using confetturaClient.EnabledWithActorInCustomSpace(...)  
   * If yes, check if the user‚Äôs **email domain supports SSO** via dfwClient.IsSSOEnabledForUser(email)  
       
   * **Platform-Based SSO Branching**  
     * If the request is from i**OS/Android (mobile app):**  
       * Block the flow due to unsupported SSO ‚Üí return 406 Not Acceptable: "SSO login not supported on mobile"

     * If from **Web/API:**  
       * Build and return a SAML login request:  
         1. Fetch SAML config: dfwClient.GetSSOSAMLParam  
         2. Retrieve SP keystore (if signatures are required): dfwClient.GetSPKeystore  
         3. Apply country-specific overrides: dfwClient.HandleCountrySpecificAssertionURL  
         4. Generate SAML request: httputil.GenerateSAMLRequest  
       * Return 200 OK with SAML request data ‚Üí **exit flow here**

4. **Fetch User Profile**

   * Use owClient.FetchUser(email) to retrieve user details from OrderWeb.  
   * This fetch includes:  
     * Whether the user is **already registered**  
     * The user's **authentication providers**  
     * Their **userID, DRN,** and **employee status**  
   * If the service call fails ‚Üí return 500 Internal Server Error

---

###### ***Step 3A: Recognised User Journey (User is Registered)***

1. **Inject User Metadata into Context**  
   * Enhance the current request with userID, DRN, provider type, etc., for downstream services.

2. **Security Check for Restricted Users**  
   * Use stickyNoteClient.HasActiveSarcNote(userDRN) to check if there are any internal flags (e.g. fraud/SARC notes) preventing login.  
   * If found, you may choose to log or halt the flow based on policy (optional).

3. **Determine Login Cohort (**auth-email-sms-login-flow)  
   * Use confetturaClient.EnabledWithActor("auth-email-sms-login-flow") to check if the user is part of a cohort for simplified login.

4. **In case**   
   * **Primary\_mechanism \- ‚Äúemail‚Äù**  
   * **Is\_fallback\_option is false**  
     * **Decide Login Channel Based on Cohort (experimental flag)**  
       * If user is in the **SMS cohort:**  
         1. Fetch user‚Äôs phone number from OrderWeb response.  
         2. Call /send-verification-code API to send an OTP via SMS.  
         3. If sending fails:  
            1. Fallback to email login ‚Üí trigger /generate-magic-link with email

       * If user is in the **Email cohort:**  
         1. Directly trigger /generate-magic-link with email

       

   * **Primary\_mechanism \- ‚Äúemail‚Äù**  
   * **Is\_fallback\_option is true**  
     * **Decide Login Channel Based on Cohort (experimental flag)**  
       * Directly trigger /generate-magic-link with email

		

* **Primary\_mechanism \- ‚Äúsms‚Äù**  
  * **Is\_fallback\_option is false**  
    * **Decide Login Channel Based on Cohort (experimental flag)**  
      * Call /send-verification-code API to send an OTP via SMS.

  * **Primary\_mechanism \- ‚Äúsms‚Äù**  
  * **Is\_fallback\_option is true**  
    * **Decide Login Channel Based on Cohort (experimental flag)**  
      * Call /send-verification-code API to send an OTP via SMS.


5. **Return Success**  
   * Return 200 OK once either the OTP or magic link is successfully sent

---

###### ***Step 3B: Unrecognised User Handling (User Not Registered)***

**\- Check for Employee Email Restriction**

* Use regex or domain match to detect Deliveroo employee emails.  
  * If domain matches AND feature flag disable-employee-signup-via-email-password is enabled:  
    * Return 401 Unauthorized: "Employee signup via email is not allowed"

  * If user has no email linked ‚Üí return 400 Bad Request: "No email linked to this phone number"

**‚úÖ Output Response Summary**

| HTTP Status | Condition | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| 200 OK | OTP or Magic Link sent | Login flow triggered successfully |
| 400 Bad Request | Missing input or phone lacks linked email |  |
| 401 Unauthorized | Employee signup not allowed |  |
| 404 Not Found | No user found for phone number |  |
| 406 Not Acceptable | SSO login attempted on mobile |  |
| 500 Internal Server Error | OrderWeb or internal service error |  |

## Event Definitions

#### **1\. Event Name: TAPPED\_EMAIL\_LOG\_IN (Frontend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when the login interacts with the email login option on the Login/Signup page  
* **Trigger:** Fired when the user clicks on the 'Continue with email' button on first page of app/web.

#### **2\. Event Name: CONFIRMED\_EMAIL\_ADDRESS (Frontend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when user continue the login flow with email  
* **Trigger:** Fired when the user clicks on the 'Continue' button on the ‚ÄòLogin/Signup page‚Äô.

#### **3\. Event Name: MAGIC\_LINK\_LOGIN\_EMAIL\_SENT (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when the magic link sent to user  
* **Trigger:** Fired when the backend service(co-account) gets a success response from the generated magic link api.  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **email** (`string`):  
    * **Description:** to capture the masked user email

#### **4\. Event Name: MAGIC\_LINK\_LOGIN\_EMAIL\_FAILED (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when the magic link failed to sent to user  
* **Trigger:** Fired when the backend service(co-account) gets a failure response from the generated magic link api.  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **email** (`string`):  
    * **Description:** to capture the masked user email

#### **5\. Event Name: FALLBACK\_SELECTED (Frontend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track which fallback option user selected   
* **Trigger:** Fired when user clicked on any of the fallback options  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **Fallback Type**  
    * **Description:** to capture fallback type ie sms/email/password  
      * RESEND\_CODE  
      * SEND\_MAGIC\_LINK  
      * RESEND\_MAGIC\_LINK  
      * ENTER\_PASSWORD  
  * Source View   
    * OTP\_VERIFICATION\_SCREEN  
    * MAGIC\_LINK\_VERIFICATION\_SCREEN

#### **6\. Event Name: VERIFICATION\_CODE\_SEND\_ATTEMPTED (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when OTP sent to user  
* **Trigger:** Fired when backend service get success/failure from send verification code api  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **success (boolean):**  
    * **Description:** whether OTP sent or not determine by api response  
  * **phone\_last4 (string):**  
    * **Description:**Last 4 digit of the phone number user entered  
  * **time\_to\_send\_in\_ms (uint64):**  
    * **Description:** when OTP is sent successfully to user

####  **7\. Event Name: VERIFICATION\_CODE\_CHECKED (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when a user is verified OTP.  
* **Trigger:** Fired when the user enters the OTP in the app and verified successfully/unsuccessfully.  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **verification\_success (boolean):**  
    * **Description:** whether user is successfully verified with OTP  
  * **time\_to\_verify\_in\_ms (uint64):**  
    * **Description:** when user is successfully verified with OTP

#### 

#### **8\. Event Name: SIGNED\_IN (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when a user successfully logged in app  
* **Trigger:** Fired when Login API successfully generate auth token and give success response  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **identity\_provider (enum):**  
    * **Description:** from which method the user logged in   
      * identity\_provider\_unspecified  
      * passcode  
      * otp  
      * google  
      * facebook  
      * password  
      * apple  
      * session  
      * sso

#### **9\. Event Name: SIGN\_IN\_FAILURE (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track when a user not able to login in  
* **Trigger:** Fired when Login API failed to generate auth token  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **identity\_provider (enum):**  
    * **Description:** from which method the user logged in  
      * identity\_provider\_unspecified  
      * passcode  
      * otp  
      * google  
      * facebook  
      * password  
      * apple  
      * session  
      * sso  
  * **failure\_reason (enum):**  
    * **Description**: to record the failure reason  
      * failure\_reason\_unspecified  
      * user\_email\_not\_found  
      * user\_password\_invalid

#### **10\. Event Name: KNOWN\_USER\_EMAIL\_ADDRESS\_ENTERED (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track registered user  
* **Trigger:** Fired when the co-account service determine user requested for login is registered  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **authentication\_mechanism (enum):**  
    * **Description:** which primary mechanism backend getting from client  
      * AUTHENTICATION\_MECHANISM\_EMAIL  
      * AUTHENTICATION\_MECHANISM\_SMS  
      * AUTHENTICATION\_MECHANISM\_UNSPECIFIED  
  * **fallback\_option (boolean):**  
    * **Description:** whether the request came from client is fallback option or no 

#### **11\. Event Name: UNKNOWN\_USER\_EMAIL\_ADDRESS\_ENTERED (Backend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track unregistered user  
* **Trigger:** Fired when the co-account service determine user requested for login is unregistered

#### **12\. Event Name: Email Entered (Frontend Event)**

* **Purpose:** To track if the prefilled email was used to login as well.  
* **Trigger:** Fired when user taps on continue (expected only from users who are part of treatment)  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **Email Entry Method** \- MANUAL / PREFILLED  
  * **User ID** \- user id of the prefilled email.

**13\. Otp Submitted (Frontend Event) \- Android Only**

* **Purpose:** To track otp submitted from client  
* **Trigger:** Fired on confirm code tap. (Expected in android for auto submission too)  
* **Key Properties:**  
  * **Submission Type** \- auto / manual.  
  * **Time Taken Ms \-** Expected when the otp is auto submitted, should be time gap between otp verification screen load and auto submission on receiving OTP message.

```
       else SSO Not Enabled
           co-accounts-->>order-web: FetchUser(email)
           order-web-->>co-accounts: User Data
          
           rect rgb(255, 230, 210)
           alt User Registered 
               co-accounts->>sticky-note: Has active sarc note(user)
               sticky-note-->>co-accounts: sarc note status

               rect rgb(255, 225, 224)
               alt sarc note true
               co-accounts-->>Client: Error response
               else sarc note false
          
               note right of Client:{"primary_mechanism": ‚Äúemail‚Äù,\n"is_fallback_option":false}
               co-accounts->>confettura: check for experimental flag for the user"auth-email-sms-login-flow"
               confettura->>co-accounts: email/sms

               rect rgb(224, 247, 233)
               alt if sms
                   co-accounts->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /send-verification-code
                   sphinx->>co-accounts: 200 OK
                   co-accounts ->> Client: success
                   note right of Client:{"registered": true,"email_sent": false,"sms_sent": true,"phone": "+912198391839", "email":"abc@gmail.com", ‚Äúsaml_metadata": {}}
                   Client->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /verify_code
                   sphinx->>Client: 200 OK  
                   Client->>order-web: üü¢ POST /api/auth/login
                   order-web->>Client: 200 OK
                   Client->>User: User logged in
               else if email
                   co-accounts->>order-web: üü¢ POST /login/generate_magic_link
                   order-web->>co-accounts: 200 OK
                   co-accounts ->> Client: success
                   note right of Client:{"registered": true,"email_sent": true,"sms_sent": false,"phone": "", "email":"abc@gmail.com", ‚Äúsaml_metadata": {}} 
                   Client->>User: Check your email
                   note right of User: User clicks on magic link and gets logged in
               end
               end

               rect rgb(243, 237, 251)
               alt Fallback option - Resend Magic Link
               User->>Client: Resend Magic Link
               note right of Client:{"primary_mechanism": ‚Äúemail‚Äù,\n"is_fallback_option":true}
               co-accounts->>order-web: üü¢ POST /login/generate_magic_link
               order-web->>co-accounts: 200 OK
               co-accounts ->> Client: success
               note right of Client:{"registered": true,"email_sent": true,"sms_sent": false,"phone": "", "email":"abc@gmail.com", ‚Äúsaml_metadata": {}}   
               Client->>User: Check your email
               note right of User: User clicks on magic link and gets logged in

               else Fallback option - Verify Phone / Resend Code
               note right of Client:{"primary_mechanism": ‚Äúsms‚Äù,\n"is_fallback_option":true}
               co-accounts->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /send-verification-code
               sphinx->>co-accounts: 200 OK
               co-accounts ->> Client: success
               note right of Client:{"registered": true,"email_sent": false,"sms_sent": true,"phone": "+912198391839", "email":"abc@gmail.com", ‚Äúsaml_metadata": {}}   
               Client->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /verify_code
               sphinx->>Client: 200 OK  
               Client->>order-web: üü¢ POST /api/auth/login
               order-web->>Client: 200 OK
               Client->>User: User logged in 

               else Fallback option - Use password
               note right of Client: Use existing flow

               end
               end
       
               end
               end
           else User Not Registered
               co-accounts->>co-accounts: isEmployee(email)
              
               rect rgb(240, 220, 255)
               alt Is Employee Email
                   co-accounts->>confettura: Check DisableEmployeePasswordSignup
                   confettura-->>co-accounts: Feature Status
                   co-accounts-->>Client: Send Error
               else Not Employee Email
                  
                   co-accounts->>confettura: Check SmsVerificationAccountCreationFlag
                   confettura-->>co-accounts: Feature Status
                   co-accounts-->>Client: User Registered: false
                   note left of Client: {"registered": false,"email_sent": false,"sms_sent": false,"phone": "", "email":"abc@gmail.com", ‚Äúsaml_metadata": {}}
                   Client->>User: Signup flow
                   note left of Client: Start the existing sign up flow
               end
               end
           end
           end
       end
       end
   end
   end
```

### **Phase \-2 Mermaid code:**

```
sequenceDiagram
  participant User
  participant App
  participant co-accounts
  participant internal-service
  participant order-web
  participant confettura
  participant sphinx

  User->>App: Clicks "Enter Email" / "Enter phone number"
 
  App->>co-accounts: üü¢ POST /request-login
  co-accounts-->internal-service: üü¢ Validate user, status, rules
  alt Email is Registered
    note right of App:{"primary_mechanism": ‚Äúemail‚Äù,\n"is_fallback_option":false}
    co-accounts->>confettura: check for experimental flag for the user"auth-email-sms-login-flow"
    confettura->>co-accounts: email/sms
    alt if sms
        co-accounts->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /send-verification-code
        sphinx->>co-accounts: 200 OK

    else if email
        co-accounts->>order-web: üü¢ POST /login/generate_magic_link
        order-web->>co-accounts: 200 OK
    end
    note right of App:{"primary_mechanism": ‚Äúemail‚Äù,\n"is_fallback_option":true}
        co-accounts->>order-web: üü¢ POST /login/generate_magic_link
        order-web->>co-accounts: 200 OK

    note right of App:{"primary_mechanism": ‚Äúsms‚Äù,\n"is_fallback_option":false}
        co-accounts->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /send-verification-code
        sphinx->>co-accounts: 200 OK

    note right of App:{"primary_mechanism": ‚Äúsms‚Äù,\n"is_fallback_option":true}
        co-accounts->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /send-verification-code
        sphinx->>co-accounts: 200 OK



    co-accounts->>App: 200 OK
    note left of co-accounts: {"registered": true,\n"email_sent": true/false, \n"sms_sent": true,\n"phone": "+912198391839",\n"email":"abc@gmail.com"}
    
    alt Fallback option
      App->>User: Resend Magic Link / Verify Phone / Use password
      User->>App: Selects an option
      note left of App: Continue with the flow which User selected
    end

  else Email Not Registered
    co-accounts->>App: 404 not found
    note left of co-accounts: {"registered": false,\n"phone": "",\n"email":""}
    App->>User: Verify phone number
    App->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /send-verification-code
    User->>App: Enter OTP
    App->>sphinx: üü¢ POST /verify-code
    sphinx->>App: Verified
    App->>User: Create account
    User->>App: Enter details
    App->>order-web: POST /orderapp/v1/users
    order-web->>App: 201 Created
    App->>User: User logged in
  end
```
